Package: zicbcf
Type: Package
Title: Zero-Inflated Continuous Bayesian Causal Forests
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-06-01
Authors@R: person("Hugo", "Gobato Souto",
           email = "hugo.souto@dell.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7039-0572"))
Maintainer: Hugo Gobato Souto <hugo.souto@dell.com>
Description: Implements Zero-Inflated Continuous Bayesian Causal Forests (ZIC-BCF)
    paired with Duan's Non-Parametric Smearing Re-transformation (ZIC-BCF-Smear)
    to estimate conditional average treatment effects for semicontinuous outcomes.
    The continuous intensity is modeled via a Gaussian BCF on the active subset
    with Subpopulation Propensity Adjustment (SPA), and the hurdle is modeled
    via a Probit BCF on the full sample.
